CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 17, 1959, pg. A15, reads: "To Live in Buffalo - Mr. and Mrs. Daniel L. Wilburn were married by the Rev. H. S. Cuff of Corinthian Baptist Church. The bride is the former Mrs. Fannie Mae Nelson.  Attendants were: Mrs. Geraldine Mott, maid-of-honor, Mrs. Vera Ghoston and Johnny Warren, best man.  Mrs. Catherine Kenley directed the wedding. - Harris photo."Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 24, 1959, pg. B5, reads: "Five Turner Generations - Mrs. Lula Turner, 95, seated front, reflects her pride in a smile as the mother of five generations.  The nonagenarian, who resides at 274 Wick St., is surrounded by her son, James Turner, granddaughter, Mrs. Lula Mae Mott; great-granddaughter, Mrs. Fannie Mae Wilburn; great-grandchildren, Johnny Nelson and Charlene Mott, and great-great-great-grandson, Terry Jeffrey Lindsay. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait back row from left: bride Fannie Mae Nelson Wilburn wearing sleeveless dress with diamond pattern and holding bouquet of carnations, Lula Mae Mott, James Turner, Johnny Nelson; front row: Charlene Mott, Lula Turner, and Terry Jeffrey Lindsay, posed in interior with floral curtains
